title: [River's Rest, Olive Grove]
description: The olive trees here are clearly the oldest and wildest in the grove, growing to a height of nearly 50 feet.  Lanterns hang from the lower limbs of the tall trees and the pathway is illuminated by low braziers. The smell of ripening olives drifts through the air.  A few stucco buildings scattered among the trees are visible in the moonlight.

paths: Obvious paths: northeast, southeast, southwest, northwest
